"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-paralympics-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 Paralympic storylines with 100 days to go until the Aug. 28 Opening Ceremony ...  Picturesque Paris: Iconic venues, Opening CeremonyThe Games begin with the first Paralympic Opening Ceremony to be held outside of a stadium.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.072536370572774e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Place de la Concorde will host the event with an athlete parade along part of the Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.549822507092744e-19, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9938637728104254, \"rank\": 0.005341849563968814, \"text\": \"Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The following 11 days will include competition at famous sites including the Grand Palais (wheelchair fencing and taekwondo), the Champ de Mars Arena (judo and wheelchair rugby), the Esplanade des Invalides (archery), a stadium next to the Eiffel Tower (blind soccer), the Ch\\u00e2teau de Versailles (equestrian) and Roland Garros (wheelchair tennis).\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 6